children.text: The roof tiling does not overhang the gutter by the correct distance to ensure the roof system can remove the stormwater as intended.
The Victorian Building Authority’s, Guide to Standards and Tolerances clause 6.05 Overhang of roofing (tiles and sheet roofing) states that
‘Tiled roofing is defective if tiles overhang the inside face of a gutter by less than 35mm or by more than 65mm’ .
This section of roof tiling must be rectified in accordance with above.
